      "description": "This 2001 BMW M3 (E46) is a museum-grade example of Bavarian engineering. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing for razor-sharp throttle response. The chassis is structurally impeccable, with a documented inspection confirming zero fatigue on the rear subframe mounting points. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The exterior retains its factory-applied finish with perfect panel gaps, while the interior leather shows no bolster wear or UV degradation. A mechanically synchronized, collector-quality specimen with a comprehensive service dossier.",
